Projects

Starcode

AR Escape Room

The Idea

Starcode is an augmented reality escape room set on a virtual spaceship traveling to Mars. An asteroid collides with the ship causing extensive damage and forces the crew to evacuate on an escape pod. Using smartphones or tablets, multiple players can work together to solve puzzles that unlock doors leading to the evacuation chamber. Through a timed experience, the game encourages collaboration and teamwork. My role as President and Founder of the VR/AR Club involved leading the development process and facilitating 21st century skills.

Process

Development started with a storyboard that depicted each scene in the escape room. 3D models and worldbuilding were created with Tinkercad. Unity and ARKit was used to implement the AR and the user's interactions with puzzles. The Starcode escape room evolved to include more puzzles and multiplayer, where the app's holographic content is networked across multiple devices.

Starcode [Beta]

Starcode was extremely successful in providing an engaging, futuristic escape room experience, aptly described by its slogan: "An escape room in your room". The next release will include more puzzles, a larger environment, and support for Android via ARCore.
